{
  "text": "A shift from \ue061-to \ue062-MHC isoform affects cardiac contractile dynamics by slowing b [CITATION_1] Figure 6 . Effect of RcTnT 1-43\ue044 and RcTnT 44-73\ue044 on E R in \ue061-or \ue062-MHC fibers. E R was measured at pCa 4.3 as described previously [CITATION_2] . E R represents the magnitude of the sudden stretch-mediated increase in the recruitment of additional force-bear ing XBs (see the supplemental text for a detailed description). (A) E R in fibers containing \ue061-MHC. (B) E R in fibers containing \ue062-MHC. RcTnT 1-43\ue044 decreased E R by \ue07a36% in \ue061-MHC fibers, an effect that was counteracted in \ue062-MHC fibers. Number of determinations was at least 10 for each group. Values are reported as mean \u00b1 SEM. **, P < 0.01. The SL of the muscle fiber was set to 2.3 \u00b5m. b and c were estimated as described previously [CITATION_3] . k tr was estimated using a rapid slack/restretch protocol [CITATION_4] . Number of determinations was at least 11 for each group. Values are reported as mean \u00b1 SEM. a P < 0.001 when compared to the corresponding groups in \ue061-MHC fibers.",
